Evaluacion del segundo proyecto de
            desarollo ganadero - Honduras

abstracts.cdata!:
The project consists of: (1) Financing
            of on-farm investments for pasture development, fencing,
            watering points, breeding stock, and stock handling
            facilities for approximately 730 cattle farms of five
            different types; (a) 100 small dairy farms; (b) 200 medium
            dairy farms; (c) 200 beef breeding/fattening farms; (d) 200
            beef breeding farms; (e) 30 small pig units, each with about
            25 sows. (2) Construction of three small municipal
            abattoirs, one medium size municipal abattoir in San Pedro
            Sula, and the improvement of one large municipal abattoir in
            Tegucigalpa. (3) Provision of four specialist livestock
            advisors to assist farmers and the livestock technicians
            employed by the participating banks, and training of project staff.
